parameters: ここで単品アイテム入手
ここで単品アイテム入手

Konoha, you've come at a good time. As I
mentioned, have you been diligently training...?
Let's see...
Hmmm... Well, I suppose that's fine.

Well then, shall I listen to what you have to say?
Is there something you want to ask me for a favor?

I've been thinking that I want to help a certain
magical girl, and for that, I'll need a difficult-
to-make magical tool...

To refine it, you'll need a total of three
materials that are also difficult to obtain. But
you'll need to defeat some tough magical beasts.
I see... so you want me to go and get it for you?

Hmm, of course I'll give a reward to each of you.
How about it?

Even if I refuse, someone else will end up doing
it, so it doesn't really matter. But, the magical
girl you want to help... who is she?
Baretta? Why her? She's doing just fine, you know.

It may seem that way from the outside, but she is
a Devil Witch, fallen into darkness.

Actually, she once saved me in the past. When I
was about to be taken down by a demon, she risked
her own body to save me.

Well, I'm not sure if it was because of that, but
it seems like she chose the path of corruption,
possibly influenced by the demons.

I'm thinking of creating an artifact that can
purify her from her corruption somehow.

If that's the case, I can't just ignore it.
Alright, I'll go right away.

I'm counting on you, Konoha. These are important
materials, so please gather them one by one for
me.

Hm? Have you pushed yourself too hard to come all
the way here?

Simply avoiding enemies and making it here won't
be enough to accomplish the tasks I'm about to
entrust to you. Come back after you've prepared
yourself properly (at least level 30).

The first thing is to defeat Ou Tora Zeo and bring
back the Tail of Destruction. It should be in the
shrine of Rudia.

Yes, The Tail of Destruction was a formidable
enemy...

Ohtora Zeo, the Absolute Guardian, is said to
appear near the sacred grounds of the past.
First, good job on the first one. Next is...

For the second one, defeat Gouen Beoria and bring
back the Eternal Flame. It should be in the shrine
of the crimson bloodline.

The second one is to defeat Gouen Beoria and bring
back the Eternal Flame. This one should be in the
shrine of the crimson blood clan.

Yes, Eternal Flame. This one was absolutely
outrageous...

Beoria of the Inferno... Originally, it was the
pet of a certain princess from a country. Due to a
certain incident, it became engulfed in flames of
anger and destroyed the neighboring country as
well... You did well to defeat it...

Good job on the second one... This will be the
last one... Don't slip...

For the third one, defeat Guhai Noma and bring
back the Pure Divine Water. It should be in Remi's
pond.

The third one is to defeat the Guhai Noma and
bring back the Pure Super Divine Water. It should
be in Remi's pond.

Yes, it was a terrifying monster called Pure
Cleansing Super Divine Water...

The foolish degenerate is the end result of an
alchemist... Trying to use themselves as
alchemical materials to create a new self, only to
fail miserably. I don't want to get close to
someone who could become such a fool...

Now that we have all three materials, well done
Konoha. Let's start crafting the cursed tool right
away.

It takes time to refine the cursed tools. Come
back after a few days.

Oh, I've been waiting. The cursed tool Flames of
Restraint is finally complete.

This is the cursed tool... With this, we can save
Baretta who has fallen into corruption.
Here, take it. This is yours.

You gathered the materials, so I'll entrust this
cursed tool to you. How you use it is up to you.
However, my wish is to save Baretta... that's all.

The salvation of the fallen... either by using
that cursed tool or by destroying it with the
power of a magical girl...

Konoha, make your own decision and guide her... If
she continues in her Devil Witch state, eventually
that power will become the power of a demon
itself.

I want to do whatever it takes to stop it as soon
as possible.
When it's over, you should come back here again.

I understand... By the way, have you learned
anything about the end?

No, after that, I gathered and organized various
information...

To put it bluntly, the mystery of the end has been
solved. The events caused by the end will change
depending on you magical girls...

That's right. It may seem like I'm saying vague
things, but the outcome of going to different
worlds has the potential to branch off. The reason
the prophecy didn't go well is because of this.

So, that means our actions are important...? Why
is that...

Actually, that possibility has been considered for
a long time. It's not just that no one believed
it.

A great power that intervenes in causality... No,
it should be called the forbidden power that even
breaks logic. Controlling that is impossible.

However, I believe that we can try to steer the
possibilities towards a better outcome.

I don't understand, but I have no choice but to do
what I can...

That's fine. There's nothing more or less than
doing our best to believe in ourselves.

The salvation of corruption... either by using
that cursed tool or by destroying it with the
power of a magical girl...

Konoha, make your own decision and guide her...
When it's over, come back here.

Huh? Is that a forbidden scroll? Hand it over to
me. So you're a magical girl named Marina...

It seems to be an altar in the underground guild
of the bustling city of Blood Moon. What should we
do?

Is there such a dangerous scroll in a place like
that? It seems suspicious. If that's the case,
Konoha, could you go and get it instead?

But isn't it dangerous? I don't think I have
enough magical power to handle it.

Don't worry, I'll cast a spell on you. With this,
you shouldn't have any problems.

If that's the case... well, fine. I understand.
I'll go and get it.

(Hmm... I wonder how many people hold a grudge
against me...)
I brought it! A scroll with a weird feeling!

As I thought. Konoha, that's not some forbidden
technique or anything, it's just a cursed scroll.

It seems that Marina, the magical girl, must
really hate me. She intended to kill me with this.

If you curse someone, you'll have two holes...
There's even a saying like that.

Well, it's a good thing no one else touched it.
There could have been quite a few victims... With
this, the incident is closed.
But, I can't just leave Marina like this...!

That's unnecessary. Well, if you're curious, you
should confirm it yourself.

Baretta should have arrived first, but... lies...
the corruption should have been purified...
right?!

I can't believe it... But I wonder where she
went...

Let's look inside the room to see if there are any
clues.

So, you're saying there were no external injuries,
which means she was killed by magic? By using
magic on the witch's flyer...?

There's almost no doubt that Baretta is here... If
her purification from corruption isn't complete,
she might have lost control and attacked Freya in
this incident...?

Anyway, we have no choice but to find Baretta...
That's the only option we have...
What the hell is going on?! Where's Baretta?!

Sorry, when I was away from here... it seems like
I was ambushed by enemies... Baretta... was taken
away by demons... probably to their base.

Please, this time, help me... If Baretta was taken
away by demons, then she will surely... awaken as
a Devil Witch...

It was my mistake to show mercy... I'm truly a
useless witch...

Flya, don't speak anymore, you might still be
saved!

Konoha, it's fine. I've lived long enough... even
before this Grimoire Land was created... I've been
alive.

Let me rest around here... I entrusted Baretta to
you...

I understand... This time, I will definitely save
Baretta... So, rest in peace...

The demon's base... I will definitely reach it...!
And save Baretta...

This wound... was caused by Baretta's attack...
that person...
It's because of me that Freya...

I will definitely find Baretta and save her this
time... Freya, rest in peace...

This wound... was caused by Baretta's attack...
that person...
It's because of me that Freya...

I will definitely find Baretta and save her this
time... Freya, rest in peace...

This is... Baretta's ribbon... Will there be a
fight here, and at that time?

If there's blood remaining, it's highly likely
that this belongs to the perpetrator. It must be
from the resistance against Freya...

☠??? Demon Beast Battle Occurrence Condition:
After Frya's death, following the completion of
the related quest.
